The President and Vice President met with Speaker Boehner, Leader Pelosi, Leader Reid, and Leader McConnell to discuss options for raising the debt ceiling and preventing the United States from defaulting on its obligations. The President expressed his opposition to a short-term extension of the debt ceiling, stating that it could harm the economy and cause higher credit card rates and loan costs for Americans. The President urged Congress to act responsibly and avoid default. The leaders agreed to discuss further and continue conversations throughout the day.